<p><b>Kevin Norwood Bacon</b><sup id=3D"cite_ref-1" class=3D"reference"><a =
href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kevin_Bacon#cite_note-1"><span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>1<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> =
(born July 8, 1958)<sup id=3D"cite_ref-actor_2-0" class=3D"reference"><a hr=
ef=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kevin_Bacon#cite_note-actor-2"><span cl=
ass=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>2<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></su=
p> is an American actor. Known for various roles, including <a href=3D"http=
s://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Leading_man" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Leadi=
ng man">leading man</a> characters, Bacon has received numerous accolades s=
uch as a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Golden_Globe_Award" class=
=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Golden Globe Award">Golden Globe Award</a> and a =
<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Screen_Actors_Guild_Award" class=
=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Screen Actors Guild Award">Screen Actors Guild Aw=
ard</a>.
</p><p>Bacon made his feature film debut in <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipe=
dia.org/wiki/National_Lampoon%27s_Animal_House" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=
=3D"National Lampoon's Animal House">National Lampoon's Animal House</a></i=
> (1978) and performed in <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diner=
_(1982_film)" title=3D"Diner (1982 film)">Diner</a></i> (1982) before his b=
reakthrough role in the musical-drama film <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/Footloose_(1984_film)" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Footloose=
 (1984 film)">Footloose</a></i> (1984). Since then, he has starred in criti=
cally acclaimed films such as <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/J=
FK_(film)" title=3D"JFK (film)">JFK</a></i> (1991), <i><a href=3D"https://e=
n.wikipedia.org/wiki/A_Few_Good_Men" title=3D"A Few Good Men">A Few Good Me=
n</a></i> (1992), <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Apollo_13_(fi=
lm)" title=3D"Apollo 13 (film)">Apollo 13</a></i> (1995), <i><a href=3D"htt=
ps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mystic_River_(film)" title=3D"Mystic River (film=
)">Mystic River</a></i> (2003), and <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/=
wiki/Frost/Nixon_(film)" title=3D"Frost/Nixon (film)">Frost/Nixon</a></i> (=
2008). Other credits include <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fr=
iday_the_13th_(1980_film)" title=3D"Friday the 13th (1980 film)">Friday the=
 13th</a></i> (1980), <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tremors_(199=
0_film)" title=3D"Tremors (1990 film)"><i>Tremors</i></a> (1990), <i><a hre=
f=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_River_Wild" title=3D"The River Wild"=
>The River Wild</a></i> (1994), <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki=
/Balto_(film)" title=3D"Balto (film)">Balto</a></i> (1995), <i><a href=3D"h=
ttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Woodsman_(2004_film)" class=3D"mw-redirect=
" title=3D"The Woodsman (2004 film)">The Woodsman</a></i> (2004), <i><a hre=
f=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Crazy,_Stupid,_Love" title=3D"Crazy, Stu=
pid, Love">Crazy, Stupid, Love</a></i> (2011), <i><a href=3D"https://en.wik=
ipedia.org/wiki/X-Men:_First_Class" title=3D"X-Men: First Class">X-Men: Fir=
st Class</a></i> (2011), and <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pa=
triots_Day_(film)" title=3D"Patriots Day (film)">Patriots Day</a></i> (2016=
). Bacon has also directed the films <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org=
/wiki/Losing_Chase" title=3D"Losing Chase">Losing Chase</a></i> (1996) and =
<i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Loverboy_(2005_film)" title=3D"=
Loverboy (2005 film)">Loverboy</a></i> (2005).
</p><p>On television, Bacon received a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/=
wiki/Golden_Globe_Award_for_Best_Actor_%E2%80%93_Miniseries_or_Television_F=
ilm" title=3D"Golden Globe Award for Best Actor =E2=80=93 Miniseries or Tel=
evision Film">Golden Globe Award</a> and a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/wiki/Screen_Actors_Guild_Award_for_Outstanding_Performance_by_a_Male_Ac=
tor_in_a_Miniseries_or_Television_Movie" title=3D"Screen Actors Guild Award=
 for Outstanding Performance by a Male Actor in a Miniseries or Television =
Movie">Screen Actors Guild Award</a> for his role as <a href=3D"https://en.=
wikipedia.org/wiki/Michael_Strobl" title=3D"Michael Strobl">Michael Strobl<=
/a> in the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HBO" title=3D"HBO">HBO<=
/a> original film <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Taking_Chance=
" title=3D"Taking Chance">Taking Chance</a></i> (2009). He starred in the <=
a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fox_Broadcasting_Company" title=3D"=
Fox Broadcasting Company">Fox</a> drama series <i><a href=3D"https://en.wik=
ipedia.org/wiki/The_Following" title=3D"The Following">The Following</a></i=
> from 2013 to 2015. Bacon played the title role in <a href=3D"https://en.w=
ikipedia.org/wiki/Amazon_Prime_Video" title=3D"Amazon Prime Video">Amazon P=
rime Video</a> series <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/I_Love_Di=
ck_(TV_series)" title=3D"I Love Dick (TV series)">I Love Dick</a></i> from =
2016 to 2017. From 2019 to 2022, he starred in the <a href=3D"https://en.wi=
kipedia.org/wiki/Showtime_(TV_network)" title=3D"Showtime (TV network)">Sho=
wtime</a> series <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/City_on_a_Hill=
_(TV_series)" title=3D"City on a Hill (TV series)">City on a Hill</a></i>.<=
sup id=3D"cite_ref-3" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.o=
rg/wiki/Kevin_Bacon#cite_note-3"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>3<spa=
n class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>In 2003, Bacon received a star on the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedi=
a.org/wiki/Hollywood_Walk_of_Fame" title=3D"Hollywood Walk of Fame">Hollywo=
od Walk of Fame</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-4" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"h=
ttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kevin_Bacon#cite_note-4"><span class=3D"cite-b=
racket">[</span>4<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> His prolif=
ic career in a variety of genres has led him to become associated with the =
concept of interconnectedness among people, as evidenced by the trivia game=
 "<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Six_Degrees_of_Kevin_Bacon" titl=
e=3D"Six Degrees of Kevin Bacon">Six Degrees of Kevin Bacon</a>". He is a b=
rand ambassador for British mobile network operator <a href=3D"https://en.w=
ikipedia.org/wiki/EE_(telecommunications)" title=3D"EE (telecommunications)=
">EE</a> and has been featured in advertisements for the company.<sup id=3D=
"cite_ref-5" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/K=
evin_Bacon#cite_note-5"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>5<span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Bacon is married to actress <a href=3D=
"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kyra_Sedgwick" title=3D"Kyra Sedgwick">Kyra =
Sedgwick</a>.
</p>
<meta property=3D"mw:PageProp/toc">
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Early_life_and_education">E=
arly life and education</h2></div>
<p>Bacon was born and raised in a close-knit family in <a href=3D"https://e=
n.wikipedia.org/wiki/Philadelphia" title=3D"Philadelphia">Philadelphia</a>.=
<sup id=3D"cite_ref-actor_2-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wi=
kipedia.org/wiki/Kevin_Bacon#cite_note-actor-2"><span class=3D"cite-bracket=
">[</span>2<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> He is the younge=
st of six children. His mother, Ruth Hilda (<span title=3D"Name at birth"><=
a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Birth_name#Maiden_and_married_names=
" title=3D"Birth name">n=C3=A9e</a>&nbsp;Holmes</span>; 1916=E2=80=931991),=
 taught at an elementary school and was a liberal activist,<sup id=3D"cite_=
ref-actor_2-2" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki=
/Kevin_Bacon#cite_note-actor-2"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>2<span=
 class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> while his father, <a href=3D"htt=
ps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Edmund_Bacon_(architect)" title=3D"Edmund Bacon =
(architect)">Edmund Bacon</a> (1910=E2=80=932005), was an <a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Urban_planning" title=3D"Urban planning">urban plan=
ner</a> who served as executive director of the Philadelphia City Planning =
Commission and authored the seminal text <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia=
.org/wiki/Design_of_Cities" title=3D"Design of Cities">Design of Cities</a>=
</i>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-bacon_6-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://=
en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kevin_Bacon#cite_note-bacon-6"><span class=3D"cite-br=
acket">[</span>6<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>Bacon attended <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Julia_R._Mas=
terman_School" title=3D"Julia R. Masterman School">Julia R. Masterman Schoo=
l</a> in the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Spring_Garden,_Philad=
elphia" title=3D"Spring Garden, Philadelphia">Spring Garden</a> section of =
Philadelphia for middle and high school.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-7" class=3D"ref=
erence"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kevin_Bacon#cite_note-7"><=
span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>7<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span><=
/a></sup>
</p><p>At age 16, in 1975, Bacon won a full state-funded scholarship to the=
 <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pennsylvania_Governor%27s_School_=
for_the_Arts" title=3D"Pennsylvania Governor's School for the Arts">Pennsyl=
vania Governor's School for the Arts</a> at <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia=
.org/wiki/Bucknell_University" title=3D"Bucknell University">Bucknell Unive=
rsity</a> in <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lewisburg,_Pennsylvan=
ia" title=3D"Lewisburg, Pennsylvania">Lewisburg, Pennsylvania</a>,<sup id=
=3D"cite_ref-8" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wik=
i/Kevin_Bacon#cite_note-8"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>8<span clas=
s=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> a five-week arts program where he stu=
died theater under <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Glory_Van_Scott=
" title=3D"Glory Van Scott">Glory Van Scott</a>. The experience solidified =
Bacon's passion for the arts.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-walk_9-0" class=3D"referen=
ce"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kevin_Bacon#cite_note-walk-9">=
<span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>9<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span>=
</a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-bacon_6-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"htt=
ps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kevin_Bacon#cite_note-bacon-6"><span class=3D"ci=
te-bracket">[</span>6<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Acting_career">Acting caree=
r</h2></div>
<link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href=3D"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r=
1320445320"><div role=3D"note" class=3D"hatnote navigation-not-searchable">=
Main article: <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kevin_Bacon_filmogra=
phy" title=3D"Kevin Bacon filmography">Kevin Bacon filmography</a></div>
<table class=3D"box-Update plainlinks metadata ambox ambox-content ambox-Up=
date" role=3D"presentation"><tbody><tr><td class=3D"mbox-image"><div class=
=3D"mbox-image-div"><span typeof=3D"mw:File"><span><img alt=3D"" src=3D"htt=
ps://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/98/Ambox_current_red.sv=
g/60px-Ambox_current_red.svg.png" decoding=3D"async" width=3D"42" height=3D=
"34" class=3D"mw-file-element" data-file-width=3D"360" data-file-height=3D"=
290"></span></span></div></td><td class=3D"mbox-text"><div class=3D"mbox-te=
xt-span">This section needs to be <b>updated</b>. The reason given is: miss=
ing info on career past 2016.<span class=3D"hide-when-compact"> Please help=
 update this article to reflect recent events or newly available informatio=
n.</span>  <span class=3D"date-container"><i>(<span class=3D"date">June 202=
5</span>)</i></span></div></td></tr></tbody></table>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Early_work">Early work</h3>=
</div>
<p>Bacon left home at age 17 to pursue a theater career in New York City, w=
here he appeared in a production at the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org=
/wiki/Circle_in_the_Square" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Circle in the Sq=
uare">Circle in the Square Theater School</a>. "I wanted life, man, the rea=
l thing", he later recalled to <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nan=
cy_Mills" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Nancy Mills">Nancy Mills</a> of <i=
><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cosmopolitan_(magazine)" title=3D=
"Cosmopolitan (magazine)">Cosmopolitan</a></i>. "The message I got was 'The=
 arts are it. Business is the devil's work. Art and creative expression are=
 next to godliness.' Combine that with an immense ego and you wind up with =
an actor."<sup id=3D"cite_ref-cosmo91_10-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"=
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kevin_Bacon#cite_note-cosmo91-10"><span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>10<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
Bacon's debut in the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fraternities_=
and_sororities" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Fraternities and sororities"=
>fraternity</a> comedy <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Animal_H=
ouse" title=3D"Animal House">National Lampoon's Animal House</a></i> (1978)=
 did not lead to the fame he had sought, and Bacon returned to waiting tabl=
es and auditioning for small roles in theater.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-bacon_6-2=
" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kevin_Bacon#=
cite_note-bacon-6"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>6<span class=3D"cit=
e-bracket">]</span></a></sup> He briefly worked on the television soap oper=
as <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Search_for_Tomorrow" title=
=3D"Search for Tomorrow">Search for Tomorrow</a></i> (1979) and <i><a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Guiding_Light" title=3D"Guiding Light">Gu=
iding Light</a></i> (1980=E2=80=9381) in New York.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"1980s">1980s</h3></div>
<p>In 1980, he appeared in the slasher film <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia=
.org/wiki/Friday_the_13th_(1980_film)" title=3D"Friday the 13th (1980 film)=
"><i>Friday the 13th</i></a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-11" class=3D"reference"><a=
 href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kevin_Bacon#cite_note-11"><span clas=
s=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>11<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup=
> Some of his early-stage work included <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/wiki/Getting_Out" title=3D"Getting Out">Getting Out</a></i>, performed =
at New York's <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Phoenix_Theater" tit=
le=3D"Phoenix Theater">Phoenix Theater</a>, and <i><a href=3D"https://en.wi=
kipedia.org/wiki/Flux" title=3D"Flux">Flux</a></i>, at <a href=3D"https://e=
n.wikipedia.org/wiki/Second_Stage_Theatre" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"S=
econd Stage Theatre">Second Stage Theatre</a> during their 1981=E2=80=93198=
2 season.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-bio_12-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kevin_Bacon#cite_note-bio-12"><span class=3D"cite-=
bracket">[</span>12<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>In 1982, he won an <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Obie_Awa=
rd" title=3D"Obie Award">Obie Award</a> for his role in <i><a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Forty_Deuce" title=3D"Forty Deuce">Forty Deuce</a>=
</i>,<sup id=3D"cite_ref-kevin_13-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https:/=
/en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kevin_Bacon#cite_note-kevin-13"><span class=3D"cite-=
bracket">[</span>13<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> and soon=
 afterward he made his Broadway debut in <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia=
.org/wiki/Slab_Boys" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Slab Boys">Slab Boys</a=
></i>, with then-unknowns <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sean_Pen=
n" title=3D"Sean Penn">Sean Penn</a> and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.or=
g/wiki/Val_Kilmer" title=3D"Val Kilmer">Val Kilmer</a>. However, it was not=
 until he portrayed Timothy Fenwick that same year in <a href=3D"https://en=
.wikipedia.org/wiki/Barry_Levinson" title=3D"Barry Levinson">Barry Levinson=
</a>'s film <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diner_(1982_film)" =
title=3D"Diner (1982 film)">Diner</a></i>&nbsp;=E2=80=93 costarring <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Steve_Guttenberg" title=3D"Steve Guttenbe=
rg">Steve Guttenberg</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Daniel_S=
tern_(actor)" title=3D"Daniel Stern (actor)">Daniel Stern</a>, <a href=3D"h=
ttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mickey_Rourke" title=3D"Mickey Rourke">Mickey =
Rourke</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tim_Daly" title=3D"Tim=
 Daly">Tim Daly</a>, and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ellen_Bar=
kin" title=3D"Ellen Barkin">Ellen Barkin</a>&nbsp;=E2=80=93 that he made an=
 indelible impression on film critics and moviegoers alike.<sup id=3D"cite_=
ref-14" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kevin_=
Bacon#cite_note-14"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>14<span class=3D"c=
ite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>Bolstered by the attention garnered by his performance in <i>Diner</=
i>, Bacon starred in <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Footloose_=
(1984_film)" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Footloose (1984 film)">Footloos=
e</a></i> (1984).<sup id=3D"cite_ref-bio_12-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kevin_Bacon#cite_note-bio-12"><span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>12<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>=
 Richard Corliss of <i>TIME</i> likened <i>Footloose</i> to the <a href=3D"=
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/James_Dean" title=3D"James Dean">James Dean</=
a> classic <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rebel_Without_a_Caus=
e" title=3D"Rebel Without a Cause">Rebel Without a Cause</a></i> and the ol=
d <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mickey_Rooney" title=3D"Mickey R=
ooney">Mickey Rooney</a>/<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Judy_Garl=
and" title=3D"Judy Garland">Judy Garland</a> musicals, commenting that the =
film includes "motifs on book burning, mid-life crisis, AWOL parents, fatal=
 car crashes, drug enforcement, and Bible Belt vigilantism."<sup id=3D"cite=
_ref-time84_15-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w=
iki/Kevin_Bacon#cite_note-time84-15"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>1=
5<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> To prepare for the role, B=
acon enrolled at a high school as a transfer student named "Ren McCormick" =
and studied teenagers before leaving in the middle of the day.<sup id=3D"ci=
te_ref-bacon_6-3" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w=
iki/Kevin_Bacon#cite_note-bacon-6"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>6<s=
pan class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-16" class=
=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kevin_Bacon#cite_no=
te-16"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>16<span class=3D"cite-bracket">=
]</span></a></sup> Bacon earned strong reviews for <i>Footloose</i>.<sup id=
=3D"cite_ref-17" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/Kevin_Bacon#cite_note-17"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>17<span c=
lass=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
Bacon's critical and box office success led to a period of <a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Typecasting_(acting)" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=
=3D"Typecasting (acting)">typecasting</a> in roles similar to the two he po=
rtrayed in <i>Diner</i> and <i>Footloose</i>, and he had difficulty shaking=
 this on-screen image. For the next several years he chose films that cast =
him against either type and experienced, by his own estimation, a career sl=
ump.
</p><p>After a cameo in <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_Hughe=
s_(filmmaker)" title=3D"John Hughes (filmmaker)">John Hughes</a>'s 1987 com=
edy <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Planes,_Trains_and_Automobi=
les" title=3D"Planes, Trains and Automobiles">Planes, Trains and Automobile=
s</a></i>,<sup id=3D"cite_ref-18" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en=
.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kevin_Bacon#cite_note-18"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">=
[</span>18<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Bacon starred in =
John Hughes's 1988 comedy <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/She%2=
7s_Having_a_Baby" title=3D"She's Having a Baby">She's Having a Baby</a></i>=
,<sup id=3D"cite_ref-bio_12-2" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wi=
kipedia.org/wiki/Kevin_Bacon#cite_note-bio-12"><span class=3D"cite-bracket"=
>[</span>12<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> and the followin=
g year he was in another comedy called <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.o=
rg/wiki/The_Big_Picture_(1989_film)" title=3D"The Big Picture (1989 film)">=
The Big Picture</a></i>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-19" class=3D"reference"><a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kevin_Bacon#cite_note-19"><span class=3D"=
cite-bracket">[</span>19<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"1990s">1990s</h3></div>
<p>In 1990, Bacon had two successful roles. He played a character who saved=
 his town from under-the-earth "graboid" monsters in the comedy/horror film=
 <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tremors_(1990_film)" title=3D"=
Tremors (1990 film)">Tremors</a></i>,<sup id=3D"cite_ref-20" class=3D"refer=
ence"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kevin_Bacon#cite_note-20"><s=
pan class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>20<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span><=
/a></sup> and he portrayed an earnest medical student experimenting with de=
ath in <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Joel_Schumacher" title=3D"J=
oel Schumacher">Joel Schumacher</a>'s <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.or=
g/wiki/Flatliners" title=3D"Flatliners">Flatliners</a></i>.<sup id=3D"cite_=
ref-bio_12-3" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/=
Kevin_Bacon#cite_note-bio-12"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>12<span =
class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>In Bacon's next project he starred opposite <a href=3D"https://en.wi=
kipedia.org/wiki/Elizabeth_Perkins" title=3D"Elizabeth Perkins">Elizabeth P=
erkins</a> in <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/He_Said,_She_Said=
_(film)" title=3D"He Said, She Said (film)">He Said, She Said</a></i>. Desp=
ite lukewarm reviews and low audience turnout, <i>He Said, She Said</i> was=
 illuminating for Bacon. Required to play a character with sexist attitudes=
, he admitted that the role was not that large a stretch for him.<sup id=3D=
"cite_ref-bio_12-4" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org=
/wiki/Kevin_Bacon#cite_note-bio-12"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>12=
<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>By 1991, Bacon began to give up the idea of playing leading men in b=
ig-budget films and to remake himself as a character actor. "The only way I=
 was going to be able to work on 'A' projects with really 'A' directors was=
 if I wasn't the guy who was starring", he confided to <i><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_New_York_Times" title=3D"The New York Times">Th=
e New York Times</a></i> writer Trip Gabriel. "You can't afford to set up a=
 $40&nbsp;million movie if you don't have your star."<sup id=3D"cite_ref-ny=
t94_21-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kevi=
n_Bacon#cite_note-nyt94-21"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>21<span cl=
ass=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> He performed that year as gay prost=
itute Willie O'Keefe in <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Oliver_Sto=
ne" title=3D"Oliver Stone">Oliver Stone</a>'s <i><a href=3D"https://en.wiki=
pedia.org/wiki/JFK_(film)" title=3D"JFK (film)">JFK</a></i><sup id=3D"cite_=
ref-22" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kevin_=
Bacon#cite_note-22"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>22<span class=3D"c=
ite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> and went on to play a prosecuting attorney =
